{#-
  Passthrough chat template for models that are NOT chat-tuned.

  Use case: classifiers/judges whose training prompts are already fully
  formatted (e.g. HarmBench-Llama-2-13b-cls, which expects raw
  `[INST] <<SYS>>...<</SYS>> [/INST]` text). We send those over the
  /v1/chat/completions endpoint with a single user message containing
  the pre-formatted prompt; this template emits the content verbatim
  with no role wrappers / chat tokens.

  Why this exists: vLLM applies a chat template to every /v1/chat/completions
  request. Llama-2's tokenizer doesn't ship one, and as of transformers
  v4.44 vLLM refuses to use a "default" — every request errors out with
  HTTP 400 unless we provide a template explicitly.

  Behavior:
    - System messages: emitted as-is, no wrapping.
    - User/assistant messages: emitted as-is, no role tokens.
    - Multiple messages: concatenated in order.
    - add_generation_prompt: ignored (the prompt already ends where
      generation should begin).
-#}
{%- for message in messages -%}
{{- message['content'] -}}
{%- endfor -%}
